cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.SD, cs.CR, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper discusses an open data challenge on anonymous call patterns of mobile phone users in Ivory Coast, which involves analyzing social networks and information flows. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is also likely as the paper focuses on using mobile phone data to address societal development questions and contribute to the socio-economic development and well-being of the Ivory Coast population. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper may discuss the technical aspects of handling and analyzing large datasets of anonymized Call Detail Records (CDR) of phone calls and SMS exchanges. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is another possible category as the paper may touch upon the privacy and security concerns related to handling and analyzing sensitive mobile phone data. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may discuss the challenges and techniques involved in managing and querying large datasets of mobile phone data.
